title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0037.xml"
addr="jms-0037"
title="Wild category">wild category</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> be an object of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>. If we may equip a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0039.xml"
addr="jms-0039"
title="Wild natural transformation">wild natural transformation</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Delta  I}\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{1_{\mathcal {C}}}]]></fr:tex> from the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-003D.xml"
addr="jms-003D"
title="The wild constant functor">constant 0-functor</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{\Delta  I}}{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> to the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-003C.xml"
addr="jms-003C"
title="The wild identity functor">identity 0-functor</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{1_{\mathcal {C}}}}{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> with an identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c_\alpha  : \alpha _I = 1_{I}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is contractible for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>(Our proof will follow that of the <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/initial+object">nLab</fr:link>, which was stated for ordinary categories and functors and natural transformations rather than wild ones. It was <fr:link
type="local"
href="mikeshulman.xml"
addr="mikeshulman"
title="Mike Shulman">Mike Shulman</fr:link> who <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://homotopytypetheory.org/2018/11/26/impredicative-encodings-part-3/">noticed</fr:link> who noticed that this proof also works for the wild/incoherent notions studied here.)</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
