expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>14558</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#477</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-477.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>3</fr:month><fr:day>14</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>To show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is contractible, we choose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{A} : \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as the center of contraction. To identify any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f : \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{A}]]></fr:tex>, we use the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0039.xml"
addr="jms-0039"
title="Wild natural transformation">wild naturality</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Delta  I}\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{1_{\mathcal {C}}}]]></fr:tex>. In particular, we have an identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _f]]></fr:tex> between <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _I;f]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{I};\alpha _A]]></fr:tex>. By our assumption that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _I=1_{I}]]></fr:tex> and using the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0037.xml"
addr="jms-0037"
title="Wild category">wild left-unit</fr:link> identifications <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda  f]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda  \alpha _A]]></fr:tex>, we may identify <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
