text="The initial reflection algebra">The initial reflection algebra</fr:title><fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>3</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {U}\in \mathcal {V}]]></fr:tex> be an impredicative pair of universes with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A:\mathcal {V}]]></fr:tex>. There we may construct a  <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-003O.xml"
addr="jms-003O"
title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms">reflection algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A_{\mathcal {U}} :{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex> such that for any other <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-003O.xml"
addr="jms-003O"
title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms">reflection algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X:{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex>, the space of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-003O.xml"
addr="jms-003O"
title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms">homomorphisms</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A_{\mathcal {U}}\multimap  X]]></fr:tex> is contractible.</fr:p>
 
   
