title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0037.xml"
addr="jms-0037"
title="Wild category">wild categories</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> be an object of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>. We define the <fr:em>constant 0-functor</fr:em> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> out of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> to be the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0038.xml"
addr="jms-0038"
title="Wild 0-functor">0-functor</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{\Delta  D}}{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> defined as follows:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {aligned}   \mathbf {ob}_{\Delta  D}C    & :\equiv  D       \\   \mathbf {hom}_{\Delta  D} f & :\equiv  1_{D} \end {aligned} ]]></fr:tex><fr:p>The above may be extended to a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-003F.xml"
addr="jms-003F"
title="Wild 1-semi-functor">wild 1-semi-functor</fr:link> as follows:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathsf {seq}_{F}\,f\,g :\equiv  \mathsf {refl} ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
